    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Strategy <br />
<br />
[1] Hobbiton Woods (Lets me have my site 2 no matter how I start, hopefully with a lack of a map) <br />
[2] Bree Streets (since I will be roaming, penalty -2 is better than Weatherhills cost -1) <br />
[3] Ford of Bruinen (helps bring out more Naz) <br />
[4] Mithril Mine (I might want to get a Pale Blade back) <br />
[5] Bridge <br />
[6] Valley of the Silverlode (healing, another river) <br />
[7] Silverlode Banks (I should have Rangers in place!) <br />
[8] Pillars of the Kings (*healing} <br />
[9] Summit of Amon Hen (Opponent may be burden laden) <br />
<br />
Legolas and Arwen are a strong starting team. <br />
I dont want to depend on The Pony to get Aragorn, or to help my opponent get him either, so three of him should make it easy enough to get him out, spares for healing. I would want all the same Boromir, but I only have two of the Lord of Gondor, hence the Son of Denethor. With these fellas I should be able to get all my Man/ Ranger goods out and though my hand keeping the flow of cards going. <br />
I want to have many river sites to help use my ARV&#39;s as I get them. <br />
Gondor&#39;s Vengeance to discard heavy duty minions, and Pursuit just behind to wound all, to help with low vitality swarmers. <br />
Athelas is there to help heal and with conditions. <br />
Sting and No Stranger to help keep the Twilight pool small. <br />
The Saga is good for the men, as are the Brands. <br />
P.A.T.H.S will help Frodo to deal with some swarms too if need be. <br />
<br />
Ulaire Nelya, Lieutenant of Morgul can help with a site change possibly. <br />
Ulaire Nertea, Messenger of Dol Guldur and Morgul Skulker will help recycle Naz. <br />
Runners are there to add twilight. <br />
I would play more Cantea if I had one more, and two of each of the Witch Kings are good to match with the Pale blade. <br />
Relentless Charge and all blades Perish are good defenses and I wish I had more Morgul Gates. <br />
There is good card flow all the time and I only double move when I feel I can afford to, even if it means a sacrifice of a companion. <br />
I try to keep the deck size down, but even with 72 they seem to always zip out to my support area keep the Nazgul coming, again and again..Bang, Zoom! <br />
